􏱭0􏱮􏱕􏱖􏱫Simulacrums􏱬
􏱩the arrow of time fragments our conception of the self􏱪􏱟􏱠􏱧􏱨
􏱩the never present moment fades our credibility and alludes our recognition from a single entity to fractured moments􏱪􏱟􏱠􏱧􏱨
􏱩we continuously observe the recent past while projecting ourselves through various expectations on the future􏱪􏱟􏱠􏱧􏱨
􏱩we exist in our subjective simulations and observe ourselves as the simulacrums􏱪􏱟􏱠􏱧􏱨
􏱩in this essay, we will explore the interpreters of the current ontological dyadic sign model to understand the validity of our constructed realties and the extrapolation of signs between realms􏱪􏱟􏱠􏱧􏱨

